properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 15 at 10:27AM CST until January 16 at 11:00AM CST by NWS Lake Charles LA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the first Dense Fog Advisory, dense fog will reduce
visibility to 1 mile or less. For the second Dense Fog
Advisory, dense fog will reduce visibility to less than one
mile.

* WHERE...Sabine Lake and Calcasieu Lake.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until noon CST today. For
the Dense Fog Advisory, from 6 PM this evening to 11 AM CST
Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Low visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY... ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 11 AM CST THURSDAY
